title: All of Jeremy Corbyn's awkward moments as Labour leader so far
text:
All of Jeremy Corbyn's awkward moments as Labour leader so far Here are all of Jeremy Corbyn's awkward moments and gaffes since becoming Labour leader By Telegraph Video 1:59PM BST 12 Oct 2015 
In his short time as leader of the Labour Party Jeremy Corbyn has not managed to stay gaffe free, infact there has been plently of awkward moments caught on camera involving the Islington North MP. 
Mr Corbyn was on branded “disloyal” for refusing to sing the national anthem during a Battle of Britain remembrance ceremony at St Paul’s Cathedral. 
Former military commanders as well as Labour and Tory MPs said he was “dishonourable” for refusing to sing the national anthem. 
More recently the Labour leader has been criticised after he failed to attend the first meeting of the Privy Council as he was on a walking holiday in Scotland. 
A Queen lookalike, sent by a newspaper, turns up at Jeremy Corbyn's home in north London 
Watch the video to see more gaffes from the new Labour leader.
